A 77-year-old woman has died following a fire at a house in North Lanarkshire.Police said the alarm was raised on Pleamuir Place, Cumbernauld, at about 11:00 on Saturday.The woman, who has not been named, was pronounced dead at the scene.Crews spent around six hours battling the blaze before it was extinguished at about 15:45.A Police Scotland spokesperson said there were no suspicious circumstances.The Scottish Fire and Rescue Service confirmed it dispatched four appliances to the scene.An investigation into the incident is under way.
